s we defined in our $n^2$-coloured generalisation\nof Primc's identity are actually energy functions for certain $A_{n-1}^{(1)}$\ncrystals. We will then use this result to retrieve the Kac-Peterson character\nformula and derive a new character formula as a sum of infinite products for\nall the irreducible highest weight $A_{n-1}^{(1)}$-modules of level $1$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 29 Nov 2019 16:56:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 20 Dec 2019 19:23:59 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 9 Jul 2020 16:31:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-10"}
